  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the efficacy of a 'new treatment regimen including
      delamanid, linezolid, levofloxacin, and pyrazinamide for nine or twelve months
      (investigational arm)' and 'the standard treatment regimen including injectables for 20 to 24
      months (control arm)' for treating quinolone sensitive multidrug-resistant tuberculosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
